// sha1.ail — the SHA-1 digest is deterministic, so its byte output is identical
// under ailangc and the self-hosted compiler. This also exercises the OpenSSL
// link path (sha1 lives in the TLS/libcrypto section). Full TLS handshakes and
// live Postgres aren't deterministically testable, so they're covered by
// std/{tls,ws,pg}.ail compiling rather than by a fidelity sample.
println(sha1("abc"))                 // a9993e36…
println(sha1(""))                    // da39a3ee…
println(len(sha1("hello world")))    // 20
